There is an Atlassian built SAML plugin for JIRA and Bitbucket Datacentre versions.  This "appears" to work for Confluence but is not officially supported so really cannot be used in a production system.



It would be great if Confluence Datacentre (and Server - but that is covered by CONF-45634) could become officially supported by the existing SAML plugin (or a new plugin created for it).

Steps to reproduce:

1. Navigate to Space Tools -> Look and Feel -> Sidebar, header, and footer submenu
2. Insert 'Content by Label' macro markup as follows, with existing label substituted for <existingLabel> into Sidebar:

{code}
{contentbylabel:labels=<existingLabel>|showLabels=false|showSpace=false|max=100}
{code}

3. Observe following error messaging:

{code}
Error formatting macro: contentbylabel: com.atlassian.confluence.api.service.exceptions.BadRequestException: Could not parse cql : null
{code}
----
Additional notes: 
* Other macros that appear to rely on CQL appear to be unaffected
* Content by Label macro works within page using the same markup
* Similar error messaging given when used within Header or Footer areas

